records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
The parties have agreed to consolidate Sheboygan County case no: 15 CF 374 along with this case.  Consolidation paperwork is presented to the Court.  The Court grants the request to consolidate the case from Sheboygan County.
On 15 CF 430, the State moves to delete all enhancers on counts 1 and 5. Motion granted.
GUILTY pleas entered to counts 1 and 5; 2 counts of deliver Methamphetamine.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2, 3, 4 and 6.  Motion granted.
The parties also move to dismiss and read in the consolidated charge in Sheboygan County case no: 15 CF 374.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of sixty (60) months.  That is thirty (30) months initial confinement followed by thirty (30) months extended supervision, on each count, concurrent.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs, including $530.00 buy money to Metro Drug;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
5) maintain absolute sobriety;
6) no association with any known drug dealers or users;
7) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
8) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination of both;
9) AODA assessment and follow through.
The defendant has credit for 50 days.
Minutes.
